sourcesContent:
// List of funny confessions
    const ConfessionPool = [
        "Sometimes I wish I were a header. So much more respect. 😔",
        "I secretly love being absolute... but don’t tell the flexbox gang.",
        "I think the padding gets more attention than I do. 😢",
        "I pretend to hate margins, but I secretly appreciate the space.",
        "I tried to align-left once. Never again.",
        "I don’t feel included in grid layouts. 😭",
        "I can’t stand sticky positioning—it’s too clingy. 😒",
        "I live in fear of being hidden with `display: none;`.",
        "Sometimes I think inline-blocks are cooler than me.",
        "Float-right divs make me feel inadequate.",
        "Flexbox therapy didn’t work for me.",
        "I’m not jealous of the grid system, okay?!",
        "Position: fixed? I need freedom, not anchors.",
        "I’m scared of z-index wars. Too much drama.",
        "I feel empty without children. 👶",
        "I just want to overflow with joy. Instead, it’s scrollbars.",
        "I once went outside the viewport and never recovered.",
        "No one understands the struggles of negative margins.",
        "Sometimes I wish someone would center me manually. 🛠️",
        "I hate floats. There, I said it. 😤",
        "Why do some devs insist on using `!important`? It’s rude.",
        "I tried to collapse my margins once—it wasn’t pretty.",
        "Grid layouts make me feel outdated.",
        "I think I’m allergic to inline styles.",
        "Did you know I once spent a whole day stuck in the footer? Traumatizing.",
        "I feel stuck when I’m absolutely positioned.",
        "I hate being overflow: hidden; it’s like I don’t exist.",
        "Z-index hierarchies are so elitist. 🙄",
        "I don’t need a border radius to feel whole. 🟦",
        "Padding is my comfort zone. Don’t judge me.",
        "Display: block. It’s a lifestyle.",
        "I think the pseudo-elements are cooler than me. 😔",
        "Do you think I could make it in the SVG world?",
        "I get anxious when people resize their windows.",
        "I’m just a div trying to make it in a grid world.",
        "I once had perfect alignment... until the media query hit.",
        "Being centered is exhausting. 😮‍💨",
        "I think I peaked in IE6. It’s all been downhill since.",
        "Does anyone actually validate their CSS anymore?",
        "I have nightmares about being deprecated.",
        "I hate being nested. Let me live on my own!",
        "Do I even matter without content?",
        "I tried to be part of a form once. It didn’t go well.",
        "JavaScript thinks it’s so smart, but I’m the real MVP.",
        "I’m not a fan of min-width. It’s too restrictive.",
        "When the flex container snaps, I break inside.",
        "I wish I could float effortlessly like a balloon. 🎈",
        "Sometimes I wonder if I’m just a placeholder in life. 🤔",
        "Whitespace makes me feel incomplete.",
        "I once got replaced by a span. It still hurts.",
        "Do I even belong in the DOM?",
        "I feel invisible when my opacity is less than 1. 😶",
        "The box model makes me feel boxed in. 📦",
        "I think I’d thrive as a React component.",
        "I wish I were a button. People actually click on those.",
        "Does anyone even care about semantics anymore?",
        "Sometimes I feel like I’m padding everyone else’s success.",
        "Why does everything have to be responsive? I need stability.",
        "I tried to flex, but I don’t feel justified.",
        "I once got stuck in a sticky footer. It was traumatic.",
        "CSS variables make me feel irrelevant.",
        "I want to overflow with content, but I’m scared to break the layout.",
        "My id gets ignored, but everyone loves the classes.",
        "Being replaced by a `<main>` really stung. 💔",
        "Is clearfix even still a thing? I miss the old days.",
        "I feel like no one understands me without a CSS reset.",
        "I think I’m addicted to transition effects.",
        "I hate being display: none. It’s like I don’t exist.",
        "My max-width feels so limiting. Let me expand!",
        "Do you think SVG elements look down on me?",
        "I think my borders are too thick... I mean, bold.",
        "I want to be dynamic, but static positioning holds me back.",
        "I envy the simplicity of `text-align: center`.",
        "I don’t trust media queries. They change everything about me.",
        "My dream is to be the center of attention—literally.",
        "I once overflowed the viewport. It was liberating. 🤩",
        "I get nervous when someone uses a CSS preprocessor.",
        "Flexbox containers feel like cliques. I don’t fit in.",
        "I’m afraid of heights... or anything above z-index: 10.",
        "I tried to be relative once. It was complicated.",
        "Sometimes I wish I could be a shadow DOM element.",
        "When devs use `important!`, I feel... less important.",
        "I get tired of being the fallback element. Can’t I shine?",
        "I feel incomplete without a pseudo-element buddy.",
        "Margins make me feel distant from others.",
        "I once got styled by a CSS animation—it changed me.",
        "CSS-in-JS makes me feel like I’m losing my identity.",
        "I want to be inline-flex, but I’m scared of being flexible.",
        "I wish someone would validate my existence... and my CSS.",
        "Do you think HTML5 really improved my life?",
        "I’m scared of being uncentered. It’s my worst nightmare.",
        "Sometimes I want to take a break and just be a span."
    ];

export default ConfessionPool;
